{"id":"pallu","term":"Pallu","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Separated, the second son of Reuben (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 5:3\">1 Chr. 5:3</a>); called Phallu, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 46:9\">Gen. 46:9</a>. He was the father of the Phalluites (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 6:14\">Ex. 6:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 26:5\">Num. 26:5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 26:8\">8</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 5:3","Genesis 46:9","Exodus 6:14","Numbers 26:5","Numbers 26:8"]}